  "body": "I this example:\n\n```\nB = {\n    contextTypes: {\n          value: React.PropTypes.integer\n    },\n    render: function() {\n         return <div>{this.context.value}</div>\n    }\n}\n\nA = {\n    childContextTypes: {\n        value: React.PropTypes.integer\n    },\n    getChildContext: {\n        return {\n            value: 10\n        }\n    },\n    render: function() {\n          return <div><B/>{this.props.children}</div>   // CASE 2\n    }\n}\n\n...\nApp = {\n    render: function() {\n             return <A><B/></A> //CASE 1\n    }\n}\n```\n\ncomponent B rendered inside A in App render method (CASE 1) doesn't see a context value. B rendered directly in A (CASE 2) has access to the context value.\nIs this desired behaviour (if yes could you explain why?) or simply an omission ?\n",
